The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Boy missing
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Boy missing
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	The eight-year-old son of an RPF head constable went missing from near his Howrah home on Tuesday. A local youth, Surojit Malik, 25, has been arrested for allegedly kidnapping Rameswar Rai from a playground near the railway quarters in Shalimar, where the boy lives.         
	The boys father, Ashok Rai, 40, lodged a complaint with Shibpur police station on Tuesday night alleging that his son had been last spotted with Malik. The family didnt receive any ransom call till late on Wednesday.         
	Malik a criminal record. A probe indicated he had a hand in the kidnapping, said an officer.        
	Rameswar went out to play with elder brother Tarakeswar in the afternoon. Tarakeswar returned at 5.45pm and told us that his brother had accompanied Surojit to the Vidyasagar Setu toll plaza. But when I asked Surojit, he denied that Rameswar had accompanied him, said Ashok.        
	Airport arrest: Inam Rai, a 35-year-old Nepali national, was arrested at the city airport on Wednesday on the charge of trying to fly to Singapore with a fake Indian passport.                                                                                                                                                          
